As offensive coordinator under Rich Rodriguez at West Virginia University and later the University of Michigan, Calvin N. Magee played a key role in implementing and managing the spread option offense. This offense relies on misdirection, quarterback reads, and option plays to exploit defensive weaknesses. Magee’s contributions helped popularize the system, which became a staple for many programs nationwide. Below is a simplified example of a spread option play call in Python-like pseudocode:


# Spread Option Play Pseudocode
if defense_shows_4_man_front:
    call_veer_play(qb_read_phase=True)
elif defense_shows_3_man_front:
    call_speed_option(max_yards=15)
else:
    call_play_action_pass()
